<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-097-061 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 003 196</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  August 1991 v4 n8 p68(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Arts andamp; Letters Graphics Editor broadens design perspective.andO;(Computer Support Corp.'s Arts andamp; Letters Graphics Editor 3.1computer graphics software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Venit, Sharyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Support Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Arts and Letters Graphics Editor 3.1 (Computer graphics software)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionGraphics softwareSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WHETHER YOU'RE A widly independent artist with a lot of &quot;twisted&quot; ideas or aserious package designer who needs to present a design in a perspective view,Arts andamp; Letters Graphics Editor Version 3.1's new Warp/Perspective featurewill turn your head.andM;It's a sophisticated frustration package that offers complex capabilities forblending, masking, autotracing, color mixing, color separation text on acurved path.andP;  Along with Warp/Perspective, Version 3.1 adds area charts and agraduated fill function, including linear and radial gradations between anytwo colors.andM;The Warp/Perspective function lets you warp, bend, stretch, and twist anytext, object, or group of objects to fit any &quot;envelope&quot; or shape you define.andO;Besides producing some interesting special effects, this feature is handy forthree-dimensional package design.andP;  Arts and Letters competitors, includingCorel Draw and Micrografx Designer, are less accommodating and morecumbersome in this regard, forcing you to perform a series of rotating andskewing maneuvers to convert the three rectangular sides of a box design, forexample, into a realistic perspective view.andM;The Graphics Editor comes with 50 typefaces and a 5,000-image clip-artlibrary; another 10,000 images are available separately.andP;  You can create yourown images or customize clip-art images and then export the artwork in colorPostScript, color TIFF, WMF, CGM, and SCODL formats.andP;  A Decipher Utility letsyou convert EPS files and color bitmaps for editing in Arts andamp; Letters.andO;Version 3.1 adds controls for adjusting the brightness, contrast, colorbalance, and gamma (light intensity ratio) in a color bitmap.andM;Arts andamp; Letters Graphics Editor is an increasingly sophisticated tool forserious illustrators.andP;  For the rest of the world, Arts andamp; Letters' clip-artlibrary is still the fullest collection of generic frustrations, and Arts andamp;Letters Graphics Composer ($395), which also runs under Windows 3.0, lets youperform simple editing operations on the same 50 typefaces and 5,000 clip-artimages included with the Graphics Editor.andO;</TEXT></DOC>